Describe a piece of technology you own that you feel is difficult to use
- when you got it
- what you got it for
- how often you use it
- explain how you feel about it

I’d like to talk about a piece of technology that I find quite difficult to use, which is my smartwatch.

I got it about a year ago as a birthday gift from my brother. He gave it to me because he thought it would help me improve my health and lifestyle. For example, it can track my steps, monitor my heart rate, and even remind me to exercise regularly.

At first, I was really excited to use it because it looked modern and had a lot of useful features. However, after using it for a while, I realized that it was not as easy to use as I had expected. The main problem is that there are too many functions and settings, and the screen is quite small, so it takes time to get used to it.

Because of that, I don’t use it very often, maybe just a few times a week. Most of the time, I only use it to check the time or count my steps, and I rarely use the more advanced features.

To be honest, I sometimes feel a bit frustrated when using it, especially when I can’t find a function or don’t understand how it works. I even had to watch some tutorial videos online, but it still took me quite a while to figure things out.

Overall, even though it is a useful device with many modern features, I still find it quite difficult to use. That’s why I usually prefer simpler technology like my smartphone, which is more user-friendly and convenient for me.
